<div class="page-shell">
  <section class="section-card" data-controller="install-prompt">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="eyebrow">Install</div>
      <h1>Install Inkcreate like an app.</h1>
      <p>Android Chrome gets the strongest install flow. iPhone Safari works with a guided “Add to Home Screen” fallback.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-grid">
      <article class="feature-card">
        <div class="pill">Android Chrome</div>
        <h3>Best install path</h3>
        <p>Use the browser install prompt when available, then keep capture and sync behavior app-like.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature-card">
        <div class="pill">iPhone Safari</div>
        <h3>Manual install guidance</h3>
        <p>Share → Add to Home Screen remains the fallback path, so the UI should explain it clearly.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature-card">
        <div class="pill">Offline support</div>
        <h3>Cached shell</h3>
        <p>The service worker keeps the shell and queued drafts usable when the network disappears.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="dashboard-actions">
      <button class="button button-primary" type="button" data-action="install-prompt#prompt">Try install prompt</button>
      <%= link_to "Open onboarding", onboarding_path, class: "button button-secondary" %>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
